{"questionId":"32463994","questionHtml":"<p>Find the smallest value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">A</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>I</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognizing that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi></math> is equivalent to one rotation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>360</mn><mo>°</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>360</mn><mn>15</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32463994","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.6b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the smallest value of n such that An=I, n∈ℤ+.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.9—Matrix transformations","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}